## 2026-02-08 — Agentic-Scriptic Duality

```yaml
timestamp: 2026-02-08T02:30:00Z
agent: orchestrator
context: workflow-audit architecture crystallization
truth: |
  AGENTIC-SCRIPTIC DUALITY:

  Two forces work TOGETHER, not against each other:

  1. AGENTIC INTELLIGENCE (provides FLEXIBILITY)
     - Contextual adaptation under variants
     - Reasoning through novel situations
     - Creative problem-solving
     - Learning from experience
     - Making judgment calls
     - WHAT: enables the system to handle uncertainty intelligently

  2. SCRIPTIC ARCHITECTURE (provides OBSERVABILITY)
     - Traceability of what happened
     - Engineering preconditions (valid starting states)
     - Reproducible behaviors where needed
     - Pattern detection through logging
     - WHAT: enables the agent to work effectively

  THE SYMBIOSIS:
    Scriptic architecture ENABLES agentic intelligence by:
      - Providing clear observability (agent knows what happened)
      - Ensuring preconditions (agent starts from valid state)
      - Tracking variants (agent learns from different contexts)
      - Logging patterns (agent recognizes recurring situations)

    Agentic intelligence EXTENDS scriptic architecture by:
      - Handling cases scripts can't anticipate
      - Adapting to novel contexts
      - Proposing new scripts when patterns emerge
      - Deciding when to be deterministic vs flexible

  IMPLEMENTATION:
    scriptic_provides:
      - Hook preconditions (validate before action)
      - Logging infrastructure (.remembrance, audits)
      - Pattern schemas (opportunity, hypothesis, test)
      - Traceable execution (who did what when)

    agentic_provides:
      - Contextual reasoning (what's appropriate now)
      - Variant handling (this case is different because...)
      - Creative solutions (no script for this, so...)
      - Meta-learning (we should script this in future)

principle: |
  Scriptic architecture enables agentic intelligence.
  Agentic intelligence extends scriptic architecture.
  Neither replaces the other; they are symbiotic.

confidence: 1.0
shape_shift: true
```

